    99: '<h2>The End</h2>',
    100: '<button class="choice" id="choice-100-107" value="107">Throw Emile out of harm\'s way</button><button class="choice" id="choice-100-110" value="110">Step back and observe</button>',
    101: '<button class="choice" id="choice-101-106" value="106">Stay put long enough for Sergei to blow his nose enough for there to be light</button><button class="choice" id="choice-101-111" value="111">Reject the story as a baseless fancy and to hurry on so you might once again see daylight</button>',
    102: '<button class="choice" id="choice-102-109" value="109">Continue</button>',
    103: '<h2>The End</h2>',
    104: '<h2>The End</h2>',
    105: '<button class="choice" id="choice-105-113" value="113">Tell the council, in all earnestness, that you intend to help find some kind of compromise between their interests and the interests of the goblins</button><button class="choice" id="choice-105-115" value="115">Tell the council everything you know of the golbins\' plans to attack Hak\'kal, such as the strange device in your clock tower</button><button class="choice" id="choice-105-117" value="117">Pretend to work with the council, but instead spy on them and report to the Aboveground</button>',
    106: '<h2>The End</h2>',
    107: '<h2>The End</h2>',
    108: '<h2>The End</h2>',
    109: '<button class="choice" id="choice-109-114" value="114">Say "Have you any photographic equipment? I\'ll create daguerreotypes of the cages and wield them as evidence. Once the press spreads the word, the government will be forced into action"</button><button class="choice" id="choice-109-116" value="116">Suggest that they return you to the surface, so that you may enlist the help of the subversives you know through your brother</button><button class="choice" id="choice-109-118" value="118">Ask to see what in Hak\'kal might be susceptible to sabotage</button>',
    110: '<button class="choice" id="choice-110-105" value="105">Continue</button>',
    111: '<h2>The End</h2>',
    112: '<h2>The End</h2>',
    113: '<h2>The End</h2>',
    114: '<h2>The End</h2>',
    115: '<h2>The End</h2>',
    116: '<button class="choice" id="choice-116-120" value="120">Lie and speak of your concern for the fate of your lost brother</button><button class="choice" id="choice-116-122" value="122">Speak candidly of the city of Hak\'kal below the sunlit streets</button>',
    117: '<button class="choice" id="choice-117-119" value="119">Be escorted back to the surface, where so many letters sit unanswered at your desk</button><button class="choice" id="choice-117-121" value="121">Join the Aboveground</button>',
    118: '<button class="choice" id="choice-118-123" value="123">Side with Comrade Eleven Stroke B. with the intention of staging an attack on the central boilet of Hak\'kal</button><button class="choice" id="choice-118-124" value="124">Side with Comrade Pneumatic H. Fourteen and see what can be done to interrupt Hak\'kal\'s communications</button>',
    119: '<h2>The End</h2>',
    120: '<h2>The End</h2>',
    121: '<h2>The End</h2>',
    122: '<h2>The End</h2>',
    123: '<h2>The End</h2>',
    124: '<button class="choice" id="choice-124-125" value="125">"...and then find a good-sized stick and begin to bash the machinery into pieces"</button><button class="choice" id="choice-124-126" value="126">"...and then I\'ll stop up the tubes with uh... with my hat"</button>',
    125: '<h2>The End</h2>',
    126: '<button class="choice" id="choice-126-127" value="127">Indicate that you\'ve done your part but that you must return to the letters that sit unanswered at your desk on the surface</button><button class="choice" id="choice-126-128" value="128">Announce that you\'ve sat and talked enough already in your life, that you\'re ready to take gun in hand and join the battle for liberation</button>',
